        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 2:41AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 241 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Columbia Bridge, or 31 miles northwest of Laredo,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Las Tiendas and La Esperanza Ranch Airport.

This includes US Highway 83 between mile markers 676 and 680.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
